<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Evel</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Teacher<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I posted this on page 5 of the nerf bat thread.....<br />
<br />
Im going to repost this as a new thread because:<br />
<br />
Im interested in seeing how some people view this perspective on the gigantic Affliction *Nerf* issue. I know that some will just flame away blindly..typical, but Im sure there are some with the power of reason here that might actually see a point in this post.<br />
<br />
Ok, <br />
Im sure Im going to lose every friend Ive ever made on this board after this post...but Enkebesh, is the only one of you whos using any logic in this argument. <br />
<br />
Now, I understand when a person is angered they get tunnel vision and its hard for them to see the bigger picture, but for everyone who is sooo quick to blame Sony about this...consider.... <br />
<br />
One of the first lessons I learned in life is...ignorance is no excuse...period. If you do not know every detail about a thing...you have no business doing anything with it. <br />
<br />
I see everyone crying out rage, falling into two groups.... <br />
<br />
1. Those that knew, some where deep down that this would be changed again someday. I mean c'mon...Sony SPELLED IT OUT FOR YOU in a patch message...sure 9 months ago, but it was there in BLACK AND WHITE. This is the group that knew the details of the effect and knew there was always going to be a chance it would change. I would say a -majority- of the player bases is WELL aware of game mechanics...down to number crunching...the effect info has been there for you to read since DAY1. <br />
<br />
2. Then we have the rest who aren't really involved with the mechanics...they wait for the hard-core players to explain things to them...they go solely on what they've been told, which most often proves to be myth. I find its generally not a good idea to trust in mass ideals...research them your self. <br />
<br />
<br />
In my opinion neither of these groups can blame Sony. Sony didn't allow you to believe these items were working as intended(as proven by the patch message that keeps popping up in this thread)...YOU let yourself believe this item was working as intended. Now, I understand this is a hard concept to understand for some...but back to my original point...ignorance of -the facts- is no excuse. <br />
<br />
I try to be as respectful as possible, especially on this board that Ive loved for info for three years. The info is few and far between now, one of the only valid arguments Ive read recently is removing the useless stat buffs from our 63-64 line-up. The rest is all bitching about this or that...it all boils down to some un thought !@#$! "Im angry because I cant "win" at EQ. <br />
<br />
Im ready to take my medicine...let the Evel flames roll, but for anyone who looks at things with an adult perspective...you must see a point in taking responsibility for yourselves on this one. Sony has made -allot- of goofs in the past. Nobodies perfect, but Id say they give you a -damn- good product and piece of entertainment for a measly 12$ a month.../shrug. I sight more than warrants this kind of..."The end is near...were all DOOMED" type 5 page post. I really think that -this one- falls in the laps of the players to take responsibility on...think about it after you calm down.</p>
	
	
	
