	<!-- message -->
	<p>There was a point?<br />
<br />
The only point I read was the silly one that said "9 months ago, Sony said it should only impact dots."<br />
<br />
All well and good, they said that.  And in response to that, people said "this sucks, change it back."  And, it was changed back.  There was no message, so people asked, "is it supposed to be like this?"  And they got no reply.  They asked again and again, with no reply.  And time passed.<br />
<br />
9 months, 9 months with affliction items glowing for all sort of nifty spells, for classes that, if the people that work on EQ play at all, would have noticed.<br />
<br />
Comprehende?  Don't try to say "they told you so"...yah, they said something 9 months ago, changed it back to how it was very quickly thereafter, never responded to people, and left something that was super obvious in the game for a very long period of time.<br />
<br />
Actions speak louder than words.  And those actions said it was working as intended.<br />
<br />
So, in my opinion, you can't blame the players.  They asked to have the change undone after the first nerf.  They asked again and again for clarification.  And then they made choices based upon what they knew.<br />
<br />
The only people to blame are Sony.  They screwed it up.  They are screwing it up now, making an unnecessary change that doesn't benefit anyone.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
