<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Tappion Zek</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I'm one of the people who started a shaman within the period between the second time they broke and the nerf. I had no idea it wasn't intended, and I'll explain why I feel the nerf is not necessary.<br />
<br />
The main issue is, our DOT's suck, even at my level (49) they aren't impressive at all. I don't like to use them, poison is way way way to much agro, and disease takes way to much time to work. I solo alot and even in that situation unless I'm fighting mobs with massive HPs, I'm not getting all the damage from disease. In groups slow is enough agro, poison locks the mob on me and while this doesn't much matter cause I tank fine, it causes problems within the group chemistry. Tanks resent me, and some groups have gone so far as to make me MT. The only reason to use any affliction item was for the other detrimental spells it worked with.<br />
<br />
Until they decide to make our DOT's viable, this nerf is a problem, especially to shamans. It's been pointed out (in group situations), it requires 5 seconds to Malo, 2 second or so recast, 3 seconds to slow, then another 2 second or so recast. Thats 12 seconds in a fight that lasts 40 to 50 seconds. Due to agro if we try to use our poison DOT's you'd prolly haveta wait 10 seconds to cast it (and even then you end up with agro a fair amount i'd wager). The alternatives are our underpowered nukes or our rains. Recently wizards did parsing on rains, and even their lure based and -10 resist rain got resisted often enough to make it barely better then their nukes. For us it's even worse so I find this to be an unsatifactory substitute.<br />
<br />
The nerf in a single narrowminded sense isn't huge, but you can't just look at it for itself, you have to look at the whole picture. In the big picture this nerf hurts alot.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
