	<p>This doesnt affect me personaly since I never had one of the focus items, but....<br />
<br />
It is NOT my responsibility to do outside research to play the game.  All of the outside resources for finding information are just that.. they are outside of the bounds of the game.  It IS Sony's responsibility to tell me of things that will affect my gameplay.  They typicaly do this with patch messages.  <br />
<br />
It is NOT reasonable for an end-user (of any product) to be expected to recall a message from 9 months ago about an item they did not have at the time. (If you had one you should have paid attention to the message saying "Hey, we are changing this!")  When I encounter an item in the game and try it out (or right click on it) and find that it does XXX, I reasonably expect it to continue to do just that -unless I am notified by Sony otherwise.<br />
<br />
I understand why they changed it. It is well explained, and makes sense.  It is poor business practice to make a change such as this without notice.</p>
	
	
	
