	<p>Fanboy,<br />
<br />
Sony has spelled out a lot of things in black and white: "Melee will never be able to bind" is probably Absor's most famous quote.  Soulbinders look like they are here to stay so.<br />
A whole new line of focus item was introduced with the PoP expansion.  This was 5 month after the infamous "working now as intended" patch message.  They affected slow, malo etc. No reason to presume otherwise.  I'm a GM potter who made those things, and advertised it to his fellow shaman as being great for slow and malo. Now I'm standing there with egg on my face, because I'm known as someone who usually knows what's going on with the shaman class, and with tradeskills.<br />
This nerf makes a whole class of foci items useless, the affliction haste.  For that deadly quickshot dot?  The other items are marginal to begin with since you rarely see the effect of an extened affliction, or great mana savings from dots.  A shaman that can make a dent in his mana casting dots has aggro to the point of quick removal from the gene pool.  And the additional tick from our poison line of dots is unreliable.<br />
My suggestion would be, change all affliction haste 4 items to 20% haste, and allow them to work on slows again. <br />
Change the AE and EA items to 50% extention/mana savings for dots.  Then people might use them.  The way they are right now they are trash.</p>
	
	
	
