	<p>By the way, I agree with the idea to tone down the percentages, keeping them between generic spell haste/extension/efficiency and the current percentages.  I think this would be an excellent compromise, because most items would retain most of their value.  The main reason I'm complaining is that they completely removed a very useful effect, turned it into a useless effect, and destroyed the value of my items.  This compromise would remedy all of those problems in my opinion, because I will not be seeing a spell haste IV item anytime in the future.<br />
<br />
They need to accept that dots will always suck (relatively), and either address the problem by actually changing the spells themselves (duh) or keep the Affliction line of foci very similar to what it has been for the past 9 months.</p>
	
	
	
