</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Evel,<br />
<br />
What I'm asking for is simply for SOE to provide better information. Unofficial spoiler sites are just that, unofficial and most are filled with more bad information than I could ever sort through.<br />
<br />
Is it too much to ask for a list of bugs on the official site so that I can know what will eventually be changed? The fact is that the patch messages are unreliable at best, they do not give accurate information on the intended changes and it is SOE's policy for their CS staff in game to not provide "spoiler" or game mechanics information.<br />
<br />
No Sony never announced that these items WILL work with slow, malo, etc...Just as they never announce anything officially with the intended effect and specifics of items. However, when these items were put into the game they DID work with those for some time. <br />
<br />
Yes, 9 months ago they announced they made a change to the function of the Affliction Focus items, and after much uproar about 1 month later on test those changes were gone, SOE was aware of it and chose to make that change live. At no point did they make any comment that this change was not intentional. And again, it is SOE's policy to not officially divulge specific game mechanics.<br />
<br />
Because of this, it is impossible for me to divine what changes they intend, and which they do not. I do not try to guess at motives for the changes, because that really doesn't matter. But until they provide consistent reliable information on the official website and patch messages in a timely manner then all I am left with are "assumptions"<br />
<br />
Baete</p>
	
	
	
	
	
