	<p>I'm a moron because someone helped me to get a coldain millitary bracer, and the first time I cast slow with it on it 'glowed'.<br />
<br />
I DIDN'T KNOW IT WAS GONNA DO THAT...I just thought it was cool.  I didn't know the effect was 'bugged'...I didn't think I was getting away with something.  I simply had an item that helped me do my job (debuffing) a bit more efficiently.  I didn't know focus items helped with slow..I was pleasantly surprised and continued on my way.  I thought ALPHA was a bug..I KNEW that FoS and Dex buffs shouldn't stack and would be fixed..but this effect never even crossed my mind.<br />
<br />
This is a massive communications gap.  What's next? Are they going to change my epic to "cast infravision'? Should I bother to quest for any item knowing that it's likely to be nerfed before I get there?   How likely is it that my 61-65 experience is going to be completely different than those who have gone before?<br />
<br />
Just a few thoughts.  I'm not angry at SoE..I'm hurt.</p>
	
	
	
