	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Evel - did I say underhanded?  Did I say they pulled a fast one?  No.  I stated that Sony from the beginning of the game has purposefully not documented most of the game.  That is part of the design.  It's why there is no official documentation from Sony that tells you how much damage any specific DoT actually does.  You want facts:<br />
<br />
Fact:  Sony purposefully does not document a large majority of the game.<br />
Fact:  Sony "fixed" the affliction items in June and mentioned it.<br />
Fact:  The fix was reversed in the very next patch after a hue and cry went out, but did not mention it.<br />
Fact:  Sony was made aware by bug reports and Fan Faire discussion of this "feature", but took no action.<br />
Fact:  6 months later - Sony fixes a "bug" causing Affliction IV items to not work on 60+ spells, and mentions it saying that the items are "working as intended".<br />
<br />
Given the above - there is no reason for a player to expect that the items were "bugged".  In fact, players were led to believe that the items working on slow, snare, etc. was a "feature" and that it was how they were intended to function.  To believe otherwise is to fall into your grey area.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />"Shammies heal like a lvl 24 Druid with Epilepsy" - The Quon</div>
	
	
