	<p>I guess this is the point where we disagree.  <br />
In order to take your stance, you have to assume that Sony is so incompetent that they would:<br />
break a bugfix the very next patch after they fixed it<br />
ignore for months the fact that it was rebroken even though it was pointed out to them<br />
place new items into the game with the same broken effect (intended for higher level spells)<br />
fix these still broken items to work on higher level spells<br />
Say these still broken items are "working as intended"<br />
Accidentally fix the bug after 9 months and not mention it<br />
Mention it a day later when people noticed<br />
blame the players for misreading Sony's intent<br />
<br />
If you really believe this, why are you playing such a badly run game?</p>
	
	
	
